cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as reference resolution. The use of neural models also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The multi-task learning approach used in the paper could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the evaluation of the model's performance on different corpora suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as well.
